[[zh:井上內親王]]

'''Princess Inoe''' (717–775) was an Empress consort of [[Japan]]. She was a wife of [[Emperor Kōnin]]<ref>[[#Brown-Ishida|Brown and Ishida]]. ''Gukanshō,'' pp. 276–277; Varley, H. Paul. ''Jinnō Shōtōki,'' pp. 147–148; Titsingh, Isaac. (1834). {{Google books|18oNAAAAIAAJ|''Annales des empereurs du Japon,'' pp. 81–85.|page=81}}</ref> of Japan.

She was deposed in 772.

== Family ==
Inoe’s father was [[Emperor Shōmu]], who reigned from March 3, 724 until August 19, 749.<ref name="kunaicho">[[Imperial Household Agency]] (''Kunaichō''): [http://www.kunaicho.go.jp/ryobo/guide/045/index.html  聖武天皇 (45)]</ref> Her mother was Agatainukai no Hirotoji (県犬養広刀自), daughter of Agatainukai no Morokoshi and her siblings were Prince Asaka and Princess Fuwa.

Inoe’s children were:
*Imperial Prince Osabe, the Crown Prince
*[[Princess Sakahito]] 

After the deaths of her mother and Osabe in 775, Sakahito married her elder half-brother Yamabe.

